# structured — PHP Project Structure

## Overview
A clean PHP project using a **front-controller pattern** with reusable partials.  
No framework required — just PHP, Bootstrap, and your existing CSS/JS assets.

---

## Directory Structure

```
structured/
│
├── index.php               ← Front controller & router (all requests land here)
├── layout.php              ← Master layout (wraps every page)
├── .htaccess               ← Rewrites all URLs → index.php
│
├── partials/               ← Reusable components
│   ├── head.php            ← <head> meta, CSS links
│   ├── header.php          ← Top bar + navbar (auto-highlights active link)
│   ├── footer.php          ← Footer columns + copyright bar
│   ├── scripts.php         ← All <script> tags before </body>
│   └── page-hero.php       ← Inner-page hero banner (used by all inner pages)
│
├── pages/                  ← One file per page — content only
│   ├── home.php
│   ├── about.php
│   ├── services.php
│   ├── blog.php
│   ├── team.php
│   └── contact.php
│
└── assets/                 ← Static files (copy from your original project)
    ├── css/
    │   ├── bootstrap.min.css
    │   ├── style.min.css
    │   ├── slick.css / slick-theme.css
    │   ├── cssanimation.min.css
    │   ├── all.min.css / fontawesome.min.css
    ├── js/
    │   ├── app.js
    │   ├── jquery-3.7.1.min.js
    │   ├── bootstrap.bundle.min.js
    │   └── plugins/
    │       ├── slick.min.js
    │       └── letteranimation.min.js
    └── images/             ← All images from original project
```

---

## How It Works

### Routing (index.php)
Every request hits `index.php` (via `.htaccess`). The router maps URL slugs to page files:

| URL         | Page file            |
|-------------|----------------------|
| `/`         | `pages/home.php`     |
| `/about`    | `pages/about.php`    |
| `/services` | `pages/services.php` |
| `/blog`     | `pages/blog.php`     |
| `/team`     | `pages/team.php`     |
| `/contact`  | `pages/contact.php`  |

### Page Files (pages/*.php)
Each page file follows this pattern:

```php
<?php
$pageTitle   = 'About Us';   // Sets <title> and hero heading
$currentPage = 'about';      // Highlights the nav link

ob_start();                  // Start capturing content
// ... your HTML here ...
$pageContent = ob_get_clean(); // End capture
require __DIR__ . '/../layout.php'; // Inject into layout
```

### Layout (layout.php)
Renders `head.php` → `header.php` → `$pageContent` → `footer.php` → `scripts.php`.

### Active Nav Links
Set `$currentPage` in each page file to the route key (`'home'`, `'about'`, etc.).  
`header.php` uses the `navActive()` helper to add the `active` CSS class automatically.

### Inner Page Hero
Use `partials/page-hero.php` at the top of any inner page:

```php
$heroTitle    = 'About Us';
$heroSubtitle = 'About';  // Used in breadcrumb
$heroBg       = '/assets/images/custom-banner.png'; // optional
include __DIR__ . '/../partials/page-hero.php';
```

---

## Adding a New Page

1. Create `pages/my-page.php`
2. Set `$pageTitle`, `$currentPage`
3. Add to `$routes` in `index.php`: `'my-page' => 'pages/my-page.php'`
4. Add to `$navLinks` in `partials/header.php` if it needs a nav entry

---

## Requirements
- PHP 7.4+
- Apache with `mod_rewrite` enabled (or configure Nginx equivalent)
- Your original CSS/JS/image assets copied into `/assets/`